		{"id":"bd2f7f843f1e9f53","x":-200,"y":-60,"width":250,"height":60,"color":"6","type":"text","text":"**sem-4**"},
		{"id":"7cfc1afb5762b547","x":-413,"y":-640,"width":676,"height":400,"color":"3","type":"text","text":"***Software Engineering***\n\n**Unit I**\nI**ntroduction to Software Engineering:** Definition, Software Engineering-Layered Technology, Software Characteristics and Components, Software Model: Software Development of Life Cycle Model (SDLC), Waterfall Model, Iterative Waterfall Model, Prototyping Model, Spiral Model, RAD Model\n\n**Unit II**\n**Requirement Engineering:** Definition, Requirement Engineering Activity, Types of Requirements- Functional and Non-Functional Requirements, User and System Requirements, Requirement Documentation (SRS). **Design Concept, Principle and Methods:** Design Fundamentals, Design Principles, Effective Modular Design, Coupling and Cohesion.\n\n**Unit III**\n**Software Metrics, Project Management and Estimation:** Metrics in Process and Project Domains, Software Quality Metrics, Estimation- Software Project Estimation, Decomposition Techniques- Function Point Estimation, Line of Code (LOC) Based Estimation, COCOMO Model\n\n**Unit IV**\n**Software Testing:** Definitions, Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC), Strategic Approach to Software Testing- Verification & Validation, Unit Testing, Integration Testing, Validation Testing, System Testing, Black Box Testing Techniques, White Box Testing Techniques, Acceptance Testing.\n\n**Unit V**\n**AI-Driven Software Engineering:** Al-assisted coding (GitHub Copilot, Code Whisperer, ChatGPT-based coding), AI for requirements analysis, design generation and refactoring, Automated test-case generation using AI, Software engineering with LLMs: opportunities and risks."},
		{"id":"42bdcf43f35420a9","x":-1200,"y":-470,"width":660,"height":440,"color":"5","type":"text","text":"***Web Technologies***\n\n**UNIT I**\n**Fundamentals of Web & HTML:** Internet basics: WWW, HTTP/HTTPS, URL, Domain names, Hosting. Web servers: Apache, Nginx; Web clients; Client-server architecture. **Introduction to HTML:** Structure, tags, attributes, headings, lists, tables, forms. HTML5: semantic tags, audio/video, canvas, media embedding. Web standards (W3C), responsiveness basics, metadata, and favicon.\n\n**UNIT II**\n**CSS & Responsive Web Design:** CSS selectors, properties, colors, borders, margins, padding, box model. CSS3: transitions, animations, transforms, shadows, gradients. Flexbox, Grid Layout. Responsive design: media queries, breakpoints, fluid layouts. Frameworks: Bootstrap / Tailwind basics. UI/UX fundamentals for web pages.\n\n**UNIT III**\n**JavaScript & DOM Programming:** JS basics: variables, data types, operators, loops, functions. Events, event handling, error handling. DOM, BOM, manipulation of HTML elements via JS. ES6+ concepts (let/const, arrow functions, promises, classes, modules). Form validation & input handling. AJAX basics and asynchronous programming (fetch API).\n\n**UNIT IV**\n**Backend Web Development:** HTTP methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE; Request/Response cycle. Server-side scripting: Node.js. Routing, templating engines, sessions, cookies, authentication basics. Database connectivity: MySQL / MongoDB. REST API introduction, JSON handling. Web application architecture (2-tier, 3-tier, MVC idea).\n\n**UNIT V**\n**Advanced Web Technologies & Security:** Web frameworks: React, Vue. Web services: REST, SOAP, JSON, XML. Deployment: hosting, DNS, Git/GitHub basics, CI/CD overview. Security: HTTPS, CSRF, XSS, SQL Injection, hashing, authentication vs authorization. Progressive Web\nApps (PWA) basics. Modern tools: npm, Webpack, bundlers, package management."},
		{"id":"78038d6707b5c974","x":320,"y":-394,"width":760,"height":364,"color":"1","type":"text","text":"***Internet of Things***\n\n**Unit I**\n**Introduction to IoT:** Concept and evolution of IoT, comparison of IoT with M2M, CPS and WoT, enabling technologies, IoT architecture and core components. Addressing strategies & Mobility Handling, and overview of predecessors such as WSN, M2M and CPS. Basic IoT networking components and their roles in an IoT ecosystem.\n\n**Unit II**\n**IoT Sensing & Devices:** Sensors - characteristics, types (scalar, multimedia, hybrid, virtual), and sensorial deviations. Actuators - types and characteristics. IoT device design considerations, hardware selection, data formats, and processing topologies including on-site, off-site, and edge/fog/cloud offloading approaches.\n\n**Unit III**\n**Connectivity & Communication:** Connectivity technologies - IEEE 802.15.4, Zigbee, Thread, LoRa, Sigfox, NB-IoT, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth. Communication protocols- IPv6, 6LoWPAN, RPL, QUIC. Data protocols - MQTT, MQTT-SN, CoAP, AMQP, XMPP, SOAP, REST, WebSocket. Discovery protocols -mDNS, UPnP; identification protocols - EPC, uCode, URIs; semantic standards -JSON- LD, Web Thing Model.\n\n**Unit IV**\n**Interoperability & Distributed IoT Computing:** Interoperability concepts and standards including EnOcean, DLNA, Konnex, Lon Works, X-10, AllJoyn, IoTivity and HomeKit. Cloud computing for IoT - virtualization, cloud models, SLA and Sensor-Cloud architecture. Fog computing - fog nodes, architecture, deployment models and IoT applications requiring low latency.\n\n**Unit V**\n**Emerging Technologies, Intelligent Systems & Advanced IoT Applications:** AloT & Edge Intelligence: AI/ML Integration, Real-Time Analytics. Next-Gen Connectivity: 5G/6G IoT, Edge- Fog-Cloud Continuum. Cloud IoT Suites, Applications in Smart Cities, Autonomous Systems."},
		{"id":"62e69c5ece99e1f3","x":-870,"y":106,"width":680,"height":360,"color":"4","type":"text","text":"***Cloud Computing***\n\n**Unit I**\n**Cloud Computing:** Introduction, Characteristics, Service Models, Deployment Models, Benefits, Challenges, Communications in the Cloud, Distributed and Cloud Computing, NIST Cloud Computing Reference Architecture, Seven Step Model of Migration into a Cloud.\n\n**Unit II**\n**Virtualization:** Basics of Virtualization, Types of Virtualization, Implementation Levels of Virtualization, Virtualization Structures, Tools and Mechanisms, Virtualization of CPU, Memory, I/O Devices, Virtual Clusters and Resource management, Virtualization for Data-center Automation.\n\n**Unit III**\n**Cloud Infrastructure:** Architectural Design of Compute and Storage Clouds, Layered Cloud Architecture Development, Design Challenges, Inter Cloud Resource Management, Resource Provisioning and Platform Deployment, Global Exchange of Cloud Resources.\n\n**Unit IV**\n**Security in the Cloud:** Security Overview, Cloud Security Challenges and Risks, Software-as-a-Service Security, Security Governance, Risk Management, Security Monitoring, Security Architecture Design, Data Security, Application Security, Virtual Machine Security, Identity Management and Access Control.\n\n**Unit V**\n**Programming Model & Industrial Platforms:** Introduction to MapReduce, Hadoop Library from Apache, Google App Engine (GAE), Amazon Web Service (AWS), Microsoft Windows Azure, Market-based management of clouds, MetaCDN, SpotCloud."},
		{"id":"ef0408991286122f","x":49,"y":106,"width":691,"height":494,"color":"2","type":"text","text":"***Data Mining & Analysis***\n\n**Unit I**\n**Data Mining:** Fundamentals of data mining, Data Mining Functionalities, Classification of Data Mining systems, Data Mining Task Primitives, Integration of a Data Mining System with a Database or Data Warehouse System, Major issues in Data Mining. **Data Preprocessing:** Need for Preprocessing the Data, Data Cleaning, Data Integration & Transformation, Data Reduction, Discretization and Concept Hierarchy Generation.\n\n**Unit II**\n**Mining Association Rules in Large Databases:** Association Rule Mining: Market Basket Analysis, Basic Concepts, Mining Single Dimensional Boolean Association Rules from Transactional Databases: The Apriori Algorithm, Generating Association Rules from Frequent Items, Improving the Efficiency of Apriori, other Algorithms & their Comparison, Mining Multilevel Association Rules, Multidimensional Association Rules, Constraint Based Association Rule Mining.\n\n**Unit III**\n**Classification:** Problem Definition, General Approaches to solving a classification problem, Evaluation of Classifiers, Classification techniques, Decision Trees-Decision tree Construction, Algorithm for Decision tree Induction, Naive-Bayes Classifier, Bayesian Belief Networks; K- Nearest neighbor classification.\n\n**Unit IV**\n**Clustering:** Clustering Overview, A Categorization of Major Clustering Methods, Partitioning Methods, Hierarchical Methods, Partitioning Clustering-K-Means Algorithm, PAM Algorithm; Hierarchical Clustering- Agglomerative Methods and divisive methods.\n\n**Unit V**\n**Concept of Augmented Analytics:** Automated data preparation, feature engineering, model selection, Introduction to AutoML frameworks, Graph data structures: nodes, edges, temporal graphs, heterogeneous graphs. Graph mining tasks: community detection, link prediction, graph clustering, network anomaly detection, Explainable Data Mining Importance of interpretability in modern ML system"}
	],
